        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p>A <em>bloodbane</em> clan dagger is especially vicious against the ancestral enemies of the clan. When you damage an appropriate type of creature with the weapon, that creature takes [[/r 1d4 #persistent bleed]] @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Persistent Damage]{Persistent Bleed Damage}. The type of creature depends on the clan that made the dagger, but is typically drow, duergar, giant, or orc.</p>\n<p>In addition, whenever you inflict persistent bleed damage with a <em>bloodbane</em> weapon (whether from its innate ability or in some other way), the weapon leaves ragged wounds. The bleeding creature must succeed at a <span data-pf2-check=\"fortitude\" data-pf2-dc=\"30\" data-pf2-traits=\"dwarf,evocation,magical\" data-pf2-label=\"Greater Bloodbane DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Fortitude</span> save or become sickened 1. The creature is then temporarily immune for 1 hour.</p>"
        },
